& [CurrentAttentionRuntimeRegistryState] is the live semantic registry for active attention
  + [registry_status] is active
  + [registry_scope] is limited LM Studio worker pilot queue selection
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_worker_pilot_queue
  + [active_frame_count] is 1
  + [suspended_frame_count] is 0
  + [closed_frame_count] is 8
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [registry_outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, worker mutation authority, broad task competence, copy-exact overclaim, and unrelated Pinky worktree changes

  = must: update this state when focus materially changes
  = must: preserve return anchors before closing or suspending frames
  = must: keep the registry semantic and visible, not native-runtime or hidden-state based
  = should: stay compact enough for context-compression re-entry

& [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_LMStudioWorkerPilotQueue] is the active semantic stack frame for selecting the first synthesis-backed worker pilot queue
  + [frame_id] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_worker_pilot_queue
  + [frame_state] is active
  + [parent_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_readiness_synthesis
  + [child_frame_set] is functional_lmstudio_lane, readiness_synthesis, one_minute_heartbeat, operating_loop_tick_014, task_frame_launch_queue, pilot_candidate, latch_set, outside_boundary, commit_receipt
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [frame_trace] is lm_studio_worker_readiness_synthesis_20260624_016.sop, 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_014.sop, LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane.sop, TaskFrameLaunchQueue.sop, and CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [focus_register] is compile limited LM Studio worker pilot queue
  + [question_register] is which real non-mutating SOP proposal job can safely test usefulness under the synthesis latch set
  + [delineation_register] is inside ready SOP maintenance candidates, synthesis latch set, scratch isolation, capture targets, validator profile, and pilot outside
  + [periphery_register] is broad competence outside, project-root authority outside, worker mutation outside, direct trust outside, automatic launch outside, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is select_candidate, preserve_source, compile_task_frame, attach_latch_set, define_validator, emit_next_tick
  + [evidence_register] is readiness synthesis, six family pass count, completed corpus queues, and operating_loop_tick_014
  + [wisdom_register] is a bounded pilot can convert readiness evidence into operational usefulness while keeping Codex in authority
  + [caution_register] is the pilot must be queued before launch and must not use project-root authority, file mutation, broad competence, or direct trust
  + [balance_register] is stable because the next action is queue compilation, not worker launch
  + [integration_register] is synthesis integrated and next pilot queue pending
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, broad local-worker readiness, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

(current_attention_runtime_registry_state) :active_root_frame: /semantic_register_set and return_anchor/ |registry_outside|
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_worker_pilot_queue
  + [semantic_register_set] is focus, question, delineation, periphery, operation, evidence, Wisdom, Caution, balance, and integration registers
  + [return_anchor] is CurrentFocalPoint
  |registry_outside| hidden model state, executable runtime stack, unreviewed worker authority, unrelated dirty files, and untracked cognition

/ [CurrentFocalPoint], [AttentionRuntimeRegistry], [TaskFrameLaunchQueue] -(EntersFrame)> [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_LMStudioWorkerPilotQueue], [registry_outside]
* [semantic_register_set], [return_anchor], [frame_trace] -(SupportsReentry)> [pilot_queue_selection], [operating_loop_tick], [balance_register], [integration_register], [outside]
